<p>I have a spring controller with the following method :</p>  <pre><code>@RequestMapping(value = "/importSocialPosts", method = RequestMethod.POST) public String importFileEvents(@RequestParam("file") final MultipartFile file,                                @RequestParam("eventId") final Long eventId){...} </code></pre>  <p>which gets properly executed when posting to the URL.</p>  <p>But if I add a <code>RedirectAttributes</code> parameter to the method (as follows), the method does not get called anymore (HTTP 404 instead) :</p>  <pre><code>@RequestMapping(value = "/importSocialPosts", method = RequestMethod.POST) public String importFileEvents(@RequestParam("file") final MultipartFile file,                                @RequestParam("eventId") final Long eventId,                                final RedirectAttributes redirectAttrs) </code></pre>  <p>As suggested by the HTTP 404 response, spring logs indicate the mapping is not resolved anymore: </p>  <pre><code> WARN  o.s.web.servlet.PageNotFound No mapping found for HTTP request with URI  </code></pre>  <p>In another controller from the same project, the behavior is correct (which would suggest it's not a higher level spring configuration problem).</p>  <p>What could be the problem here?</p>